ans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Josie Madoc","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1557,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"70716","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/70716/db241ca1-a362-4799-9090-ef1804f85ab6.png","tw":"\"JoboMa\""},{"n":"Livvy Gibbs","p":"Green Party","v":1269,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"118821","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/118821/f0c6c6d0-1432-4644-8f28-a5a9d79d6f17.png"},{"n":"Stephen Bird","p":"Reform UK","v":224,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"119495"},{"n":"June Reid","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":125,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"112869","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/112869/85b3fc7a-8e1a-4523-8b3a-df8115333dea.png"},{"n":"Martin McGrath","p":"Labour","v":123,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"15823"}],"female_count":3,"male_count":2,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Colney Heath","seats":1,"turnout_pct":44.27,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Chris Brazier","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":413,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","inc":true,"pid":"55876","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/55876.png","stmt":"Chris Brazier has impressed many with his strong community values and determination to get things done for Colney Heath since first getting elected in 2003.\r\n\r\nChris’s priorities for the district council going forward are to protect the Green Belt and to deliver more funding for road repairs.\r\n\r\nHe said: “I’ve been overwhelmed by the support I’ve received so far - it really is humbling.”"},{"n":"Frances Leonard","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":225,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"55926","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/55926/2b7b2719-3af0-43ee-9b6b-81658dbb5601.png"},{"n":"Mark Geoffrey Woolhouse","p":"Reform UK","v":223,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127636"},{"n":"Rebecca Watters","p":"Green Party","v":80,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127635"},{"n":"Iain Grant","p":"Labour","v":30,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"37093"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Cunningham","seats":1,"turnout_pct":40.5,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Robert Francis Donald","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1262,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"55880","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/55880/d75f2e1c-cecc-4fc5-a2e8-cd62b83cca01.png","stmt":"First elected in 1980, Robert Donald has impressed many with his strong community values and determination to get things done for our area.\r\n\r\nRobert’s priorities for the district council going forward include delivering more homes that local people can actually afford while protecting the Green Belt.\r\n\r\nHe said: “There’s so much more I want to achieve for our community. I feel like the job is only half complete.”"},{"n":"James Ian Humphrey","p":"Reform UK","v":351,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127639"},{"n":"Isabelle Habib","p":"Green Party","v":328,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127638","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127638/87b39bf0-3f5a-4ee4-be1c-8c87ac2a1d32.png"},{"n":"Rachael Drewitt","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":251,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"89747"},{"n":"John Paton","p":"Labour","v":142,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"15762"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Harpenden East","seats":1,"turnout_pct":42.86,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Pip Liver","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1107,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"low","inc":true,"pid":"55883","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/55883/ecaef06e-6598-4e6c-9359-81fac27bd37a.png"},{"n":"Geoffrey Newman","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":675,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"55884"},{"n":"Thomas Oliver Cooney","p":"Reform UK","v":327,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127871","stmt":"Harpenden born and raised, St George's educated, and not going anywhere.\n\nI am a training teaching assistant with experience within the pensions sector, meaning that I am well aware of the two major concerns for the average individual: what will happen to their future, and what will happen to the next generation's future.\nWithin the last twelve months, I have volunteered my time to the Harpenden Trust, working alongside many others to raise money and ensure that those people in our community who most need it get help. This has made it very clear to me just what matters to this community and just where its needs lie\n.\nWhen running for council in 2022-23, I was able to secure 26% of the vote with my first attempt at campaigning. From this, I gained an insight into the needs of this community, learning that the residents believe in a town where doing business is possible, a valued greenbelt, and a thriving high street. This is what I am trying to protect. However, I also feel that there must be honesty – Harpenden needs to remain a town where the next generation can flourish and build their lives.\nOur council is chronically under-represented when it comes to younger voices, and I'd like to change that — not to replace the experience already round the table, but to sit alongside it."},{"n":"Lesley Baker","p":"Green Party","v":248,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"26600"},{"n":"Neil Mulcock","p":"Labour","v":110,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"98173"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Harpenden North & Rural","seats":1,"turnout_pct":44.28,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Kevin Timmons","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1088,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127930","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127930/1a914f19-a330-49fe-b8a0-867155df39ef.png"},{"n":"Sam Spiri","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":812,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"112855","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/112855/ebc77639-117e-4211-9e09-be9503e97245.png"},{"n":"Philip Martin Wells","p":"Reform UK","v":428,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"119491","stmt":"I'm now retired, but effectively had two careers. For the first half I worked in metallurgy, often with high temperature materials such as tungsten and molybdenum. I changed careers after predatory pricing from China deliberately destroyed that industry in the UK. I then worked in IT, first for a major software company and then for the world's leading cyber security company. There I found the UK's companies are constantly attacked by states such as China, Russia, North Korea and Iran. There are countries out there actively hostile to the UK – we need to recognize that.\n\nI have also watched the UK change beyond recognition. Successive governments have become increasingly divorced from what the bulk of the UK wants. Both Labour and the Tories have lived well beyond the country's means, piling up debt it will take a generation to reduce. We have mortgaged our future by spending hundreds of millions of pounds a day we don't have.\n\nThe second issue is mass immigration. The UK has a long and proud tradition of offering political asylum. Until 2004, this was 50,000 a year – a level the country could easily accept. Now, because of Labour and the Tories allowing a mass of economic migrants in, it's many hundreds of thousands annually. The 2021 census (see https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/sources/census_2021) gives the country of birth of English residents. 6.6% are from the EU, 2.8% from Africa, 5.7% from the Middle East and Asia and 1.4% from the Caribbean. Nearly 17% - about one in six people in England were not born here. That's a level of economic migration (people coming here for a better standard of living) that the country cannot sustain.\n\nIt's time to put in place a government that respects the wishes of the silent majority. That means managing the public finances the same way you manage your household finances – by avoiding piling up debt. It also means cutting back the level of immigration to a level the country can sustain. And the only government that will do that is a"},{"n":"Joel Crichton","p":"Green Party","v":250,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127929"},{"n":"Ben Dearman","p":"Labour","v":96,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"98178"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Harpenden South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":49.39,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"David Heritage","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1185,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"15788","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/15788/06aff1f9-d0e9-4489-a619-551f5d127fd3.png"},{"n":"Nikolaus Rath","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":898,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"128069"},{"n":"Matthew David Swan","p":"Reform UK","v":388,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"128070","stmt":"My name is Matt Swan. I grew up in St Albans leaving school at 15 with no qualifications. Working my way up in the construction industry, at the age of 39 I became COO of Alfred McAlpine PLC. \nFor the last 25 years I have run my own house building and development business in the Midlands, also working as a partner with turnaround venture capitalist Rcapital\nI have been a Harpenden resident for 30 years and now I am semi-retired I am looking forward to putting something back into my community."},{"n":"Tanja Brueckmann-Rath","p":"Green Party","v":195,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"118820"},{"n":"Guy Thomas","p":"Labour","v":109,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128071"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Harpenden West","seats":1,"turnout_pct":50.93,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Aaron Jacob","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1290,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"67589","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/67589/afe213d1-0528-43d7-920e-34f34b331b0e.png","stmt":"My priorities:  I will back you and your family.  As your MP, I will:  1. Regenerate our area by boosting investment and jobs;  2. Cut the cost of living, by voting for measures which reduce tax and inflation;  3. Help small businesses by reducing red tape and taxes on business;  4. Reduce anti-social behaviour by working with the Police and the community;  5. Invest in health and social care, so we all get the care we need when we need it;  6. Protect our green spaces and our trees. \n\nAbout me: I previously worked in industry on the project of building full-fibre broadband right across the UK, dealing with the regulator, central and local government. I understand how critical connectivity is to our daily lives. I am now a solicitor, fighting for my clients every single day.\n\nI have been a local Councillor, fighting hard for residents on issues such as speeding, cutting local crime and protecting green spaces. I was previously a Trustee of a local museum.\n\nComing from a small business background, I am particularly passionate about helping small businesses to grow, employ more people and succeed.\n\nIn my spare time, I am a runner. I have completed a marathon, half-marathon and several 10ks.","tw":"\"Aaron_Jacob91\"","url":"\"https://www.aaronjacob.co.uk/\""},{"n":"Ric Belfield","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1270,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"128079"},{"n":"Paul Stuart Brayley","p":"Reform UK","v":305,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"128080","stmt":"I recently retired from Brayleys Cars Ltd  where I was the founder and CEO. I led the growth from a single site operation in St Albans to a £400 million turnover multi franchised business  with 31 dealerships from the north of Manchester to the south of London. \nThrough disciplined acquisitions, strong manufacturer partnerships and a relentless focus on operational performance , culture and governance.\nI love living in Harpenden which I have done since 2014 and have a relationship with the town going back to 2011 when I turned the derelict site next to BP into the Kia car dealership it is today. Creating over 30 jobs locally along with a nice place to buy or have your car maintained !\nSo, having time on my hands I would now like to give back to the community I live in by applying the practical business skills I have developed over a lifetime, to partaking in the more effective running of our local council should I be so lucky as to be elected."},{"n":"Mario May","p":"Green Party","v":220,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"5393","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/26533.png","tw":"\"DrMarioMay\"","bd":"1959"},{"n":"David Crew","p":"Labour","v":108,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128081"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Hill End","seats":1,"turnout_pct":45.76,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Jamie Day","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1615,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"36886","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/36886/1399f2f8-1a3a-4896-8cc0-7f918953bb43.png"},{"n":"Marianne Jordan","p":"Green Party","v":343,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"89816"},{"n":"Caspar Hugo Issac Thomas","p":"Reform UK","v":293,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128109"},{"n":"Sudha Bharadia","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":234,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"89813","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/89813/d38718f7-445c-4845-b8f9-87a3a7e2e4b5.png"},{"n":"Steve Clark","p":"Labour","v":97,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"89814"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"London Colney","seats":1,"turnout_pct":42.03,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Tony Lillico","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":872,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"26578","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/26578/adfc9a0e-0005-4018-b239-aaad34403eaa.png","stmt":"Local businessman Tony Lillico has lived in London Colney since 1998, and has an extensive background working in telecoms. Currently self-employed, Tony is passionate about defending the interests of local people in London Colney. \n\nTony believes strongly in delivering real change, from improving care for the elderly to providing more school places. Tony also wants much greater action on roads and pavements, including more street cleaning, and having 20mph zones in town centres.","tw":"\"TonyLillico\""},{"n":"Eleanor Frances Jackson","p":"Reform UK","v":632,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"112857","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/112857/10404f41-788d-462b-887b-4dbee1370fe2.png"},{"n":"David Eaton","p":"Labour","v":563,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128052","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128052/bbd86229-161a-4d0d-9e3e-b788618e8b4d.png"},{"n":"Sarah Lister","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":226,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128053"},{"n":"Aimee Crompton-Smith","p":"Green Party","v":203,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"128051"}],"female_count":3,"male_count":2,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Marshalswick East & Jersey Farm","seats":1,"turnout_pct":46.92,"results_url":"https://www.stalbans.gov.uk/news/results-thursday-7-may-elections-will-appear-here-friday-8-may","candidates":[{"n":"Lorraine Helen Kirby","p":"Liberal Democra